attributes.Long form description: The student is taking apart a shelf. He places the shelf horizontally on the table and begins to unscrew the wheels. Once the wheels are off, then flips the shelf over and continue unscrewing. The student then slides the shelf across the room and begins to unscrew the hexagonal cap nuts on the grid tray. Then does this for all the grid trays, including the top grid tray. The student then stands on the shelf and removes the grid trays. The student then disassembles the bottom grid tray.

attributes.Transcription: Hello and welcome to our study, in front of you, you will see a bathroom shelving from IKEA.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the wheels from the shelf.
The student disassembles the middle grid tray.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student has to unscrew the middle grid tray first.

attributes.Transcription: Please now unscrew the middle shelf.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the top grid tray.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student drops the wrench by accident.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the top and middle tray.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student has to stand up the shelf to remove the trays.

attributes.Transcription: Please place the shelving vertically on the table before you removing the shelves.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the bottom tray.
The student disassembles the half frames.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
